name: Perched on the Castle Roof
description: This moon is found atop the back right side of the castle roof, climb the small spire to grab the moon

name: Pops Out of the Tail
description: Towards the bottom side of the kingdom, at the end of the little stream that runs through the kingdom you will find a tree with a branch in the shape of a Tanooki tail, throw out and hold cappy on the tail to activate the moon

name: Caught Hopping at Peach's Castle!
description: In the flower garden section on the east side of the kingdom you will find a bunny hopping around, capture the bunny to grab the moon

name: Gardening for Toad: Garden Seed
description: This seed is the seed right beside and closest to the west side of the flower garden

name: Gardening for Toad: Field Seed
description: This seed is the seed towards the east of the odyssey amongst the trees

name: Gardening for Toad: Pasture Seed
description: This seed is the seed towards the south side of the sheep pen right besides the single tree

name: Gardening for Toad: Lake Seed
description: This seed is the seed found under water at the bottom of the lake below dorrie

name: Grow a Flower Garden
description: This moon can be found towards the north side of the flower garden, spinthrow in the middle of the circular pattern of flowers to activate the moon

name: Mushroom Kingdom Timer Challenge
description: This moon can be activated by throwing cappy on the scarecrow towards the north side of the flower garden, then continuing to head north west to grab the moon that spawns

name: Found at Peach's Castle! Good Dog!
description: The dog can be found near the crazy cap store, throw cappy at it to activate it, once it unveils the first dig spot, lead it almost directly south to the second dig spot where it will dig up the moon

name: Taking Notes: Around the Well
description: This moon can be found on the east side of the castle, enter the pipe and collect all the music notes to activate the moon

name: Herding Sheep at Peach's Castle
description: This moon is activated by luring all 6 sheep into the pen on the east side of the kingdom. These sheep can be found in quadrants : C4, D4, D2 then A4, A2 & B2

name: Gobbling Fruit with Yoshi
description: This moon is collected by capturing yoshi from on top of the castle, then going around and eating the first third of the fruits

name: Yoshi's Second Helping!
description: This moon is collected by capturing yoshi from on top of the castle, then going around and eating the second third of the fruits

name: Yoshi's All Filled Up!
description: This moon is collected by capturing yoshi from on top of the castle, then going around and eating the final third of the fruits

name: Love at Peach's Castle
description: This moon is acquired by capturing a goomba and getting it over to goombette on the back side of the castle. If you jump onto, then shake jump off of a slope, you can jump over to her without needing to drain the mote and create a big goomba stack

name: Toad Defender
description: This moon is collected by capturing a goomba and leading it up the hill towards the north east side of the castle, scaring off the toad, then heading into the hole to grab the moon

name: Forever Onward, Captain Toad!
description: This moon is acquired by talking to Captain Toad who is situated on top of the Crazy Cap store by the odyssey

name: Jammin' in the Mushroom Kingdom
description: Head slightly north west of the odyssey and you will see a toad jamming out and wearing headphones, speak to him and select any 8-bit track to get the moon

name: Shopping Near Peach's Castle
description: This moon is purchased at the Crazy Cap store near the odyssey

name: Mushroom Kingdom Regular Cup
description: This moon is the first koopa freerunning moon

name: Mushroom Kingdom Master Cup
description: This moon is the second koopa freerunning mood

name: Picture Match: Basically Mario
description: This moon is the first Mario picture match moon which can be found by capturing the rocket on the far north east side of the kingdom and getting at least 60 points

name: Picture Match: A Stellar Mario!
description: This moon is the second Mario picture match moon which can be found by capturing the rocket on the far north east side of the kingdom and getting at least 80 points

name: Light from the Ceiling
description: This moon is activated by entering the castle, standing on the sun carpet, entering first person and looking up at the roof

name: Loose-Tile Trackdown
description: This moon is activated by going around the inside of the castle and groundpounding the 8 tiles one by one that pop out from the floor

name: Totally Classic!
description: This outfit room can be entered by wearing the Mario 64 costume and talking to the toad on the north side of the kingdom. Then throwing cappy on top of the star in the middle of the room to activate the moon

name: Courtyard Chest Trap
description: This outfit room can be entered by wearing the Mario 64 costume and talking to the toad on the north side of the kingdom. Then activating the chests in the specified order

name: Yoshi's Feast in the Sea of Clouds
description: This moon can be found within the pipe subarea found on the south east side of the flower garden. Then once inside going around as yoshi and eating all of the apples

name: Sunken Star in the Sea of Clouds
description: This moon can be found within the pipe subarea found on the south east side of the flower garden. Then once inside, heading towards the left and collecting the moon hidden in the fog

name: Secret 2D Treasure
description: This moon can be found within the well subarea on the east side of the kingdom. Once inside, this moon can be found all the way at the end of the subarea

name: 2D Boost from Bullet Bill
description: This moon can be found within the well subarea on the east side of the kingdom. Once inside, this moon can be found about half way through the kingdom and is acquired by bouncing off a bullet bill

name: Tussle in Tostarena: Rematch
description: This moon is the Knucklotec refight found in the cap door of the tower on the south west side of the kingdom, near the sheep pen.

name: Struggle in Steam Gardens: Rematch
description: This moon is the Torkdrift refight found in the cap door of the tower on the north side of the castle, on top of the tall platform.

name: Dust-Up in New Donk City: Rematch
description: This moon is the Mechawiggler refight found in the cap door of the tower on the south east side of the flower garden

name: Battle in Bubblaine: Rematch
description: This moon is the Brigadier Mollusque-Lanceur III, Dauphin of Bubblaine refight, found in the pipe at the bottom of the lake

name: Blowup at Mount Volbono: Rematch
description: This moon is the Cookatiel refight found in the cap door of the tower on the east side of the lake area

name: Rumble in Crumbleden: Rematch
description: This moon is the Ruined Dragon reight found in the pipe usually underwater at the bottom of the mote on the east side of the castle. You will need to drain the mote and collect the fruit as yoshi before you can enter

name: Secret Path to Peach's Castle!
description: This moon is acquired by entering the mushroom painting in Luncheon kingdom, then making your way on top of the chimney

name: A Tourist in the Mushroom Kingdom!
description: This moon is acquired by talking to the tourist who can be found near the taxi next to the shop. This taxi will only be here if you're gotten all the previous taxi moons up until this point

name: Found with Mushroom Kingdom Art
description: This moon is acquired by talking to the tourist who can be found near the taxi next to the shop. This taxi will only be here if you're gotten all the previous taxi moons up until this point

name: Hat-and-Seek: Mushroom Kingdom
description: This moon is acquired by talking to the Happy Cappy on a toad found between some trees on the far north west side of the kingdom

name: Princess Peach, Home Again!
description: Once you have talked to Peach in every kingdom she visits, head up to the balcony of the castle and Peach will be waiting, talk to her to get this moon

name: Rescue Princess Peach
description: This moon is unlocked when you beat the game and talk to toadette

name: Achieve World Peace
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have achieved peace in all kingdoms

name: Power Moon Knight
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 100 power moons

name: Power Moon Wizard
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 300 power moons

name: Power Moon Ruler
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 600 power moons

name: Regional Coin Shopper
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have bought 13 things using purple coins

name: Flat Moon Finder
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 8-bit moons

name: Flat Moon Fanatic
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 20 8-bit moons

name: Treasure Chest Hunter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 moons from chests

name: Super Treasure Chest Hunter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 25 moons from chests

name: Note-Collecting World Tour
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 notes moons

name: Note-Collecting Space Tour
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 20 notes moons

name: Timer Challenge Amateur
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 timer challenge moons

name: Timer Challenge Professional
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 25 timer challenge moons

name: Captain Toad Meeter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 captain toad moons

name: Captain Toad Greeter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 captain toad moons

name: Touring with Princess Peach
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 Peach moons

name: Globe-Trotting with Princess Peach
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 Peace moons

name: Master Sheep Herder
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 4 sheep hearding moons

name: Gaga for Goombette
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 Goombette moons

name: Lakitu Fishing Trip
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 3 fishing moons

name: Flower-Growing Guru
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 seed moons

name: Flower-Growing Sage
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 seed moons

name: Running with Rabbits
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 rabbit moons

name: Racing with Rabbits
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 rabbit moons

name: Ground Pound Instructor
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 ground pound moons

name: Ground Pound Professor
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 45 ground pound moons

name: Rad Hatter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 3 moons by throwing cappy on things

name: Super Rad Hatter
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 moons by throwing cappy on things

name: Traveling-Bird Herder
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 bird moons

name: Wearing It Well!
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 3 outfit moons

name: Wearing It Great!
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 8 outfit moons

name: Wearing It Perfect!
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 outfit moons

name: Hat-Seeking Missile
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 Happy Cappy moons

name: Music Maestro
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 music toad moons

name: Art Enthusiast
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 hint art moons

name: Art Investigator
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 hint art moons

name: Slots Machine
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 3 slots moons

name: Koopa Freerunning MVP
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 koopa freerunning moons

name: Koopa Freerunning Hall of Famer
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 22 koopa freerunning moons

name: Supernaturally Sure-Footed
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5 koopa trace walking moons

name: Quizmaster
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 3 sphynx moons

name: Souvenir Sampler
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10 souvenirs and stickers

name: Souvenir Sleuth
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 20 souvenirs and stickers

name: Souvenir Savant
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 40 souvenirs and stickers

name: Capturing Novice
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have captured 20 things

name: Capturing Apprentice
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have captured 35 things

name: Capturing Master
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have captured 45 things

name: Hat Maven
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 hats

name: Hat Icon
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 35 hats

name: Fashion Maven
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 15 outfits

name: Fashion Icon
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 35 outfits

name: Moon Rock Liberator
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have opened 14 moon rocks

name: World Warper
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have gone through 10 paintings

name: Checkpoint Flagger
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 40 checkpoints

name: Checkpoint Flag Enthusiast
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 80 checkpoints

name: Loaded with Coins
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 1000 coins total

name: Rolling in Coins
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 5000 coins total

name: Swimming in Coins
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have collected 10,000 coins total

name: Jump! Jump! Jump!
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have jumped 10,000 times

name: Fly, Cappy, Fly!
description: This moon is given by toadette one you have thrown cappy 5000 times

name: Frog-Jumping Above the Fog
description: This Moon is towards the bottom of cap kingdom and is acquired by capturing a frog and knocking open an invisible block

name: Frog-Jumping from the Top Deck
description: This Moon is towards the bottom the central plaza part of the kingdom and is acquired by capturing a frog and jumping on top of one of the little hat houses

name: Cap Kingdom Timer Challenge 1
description: This Moon is started by activating the scarecrow towards the right side of the horizontal bridge towards the top of the kingdom

name: Good Evening, Captain Toad!
description: This Moon is can be found atop the Top Hat Tower

name: Shopping in Bonneton
description: This Moon is located in the middle of the central plaza at the shop

name: Skimming the Poison Tide
description: This Moon is located in the cap door behind and below Top Hat Tower.\nThis moon is the shards moon, NOT the secret moon

name: Slipping Through the Poison Tide
description: This Moon is located in the cap door behind and below Top Hat Tower.\nThis moon is the secret moon, NOT the shards moon

name: Push-Block Peril
description: This Moon is located in the cap door on the north side of Top Hat Tower.\nThis moon is the main moon, NOT the secret moon

name: Hidden Among the Push-Blocks
description: This Moon is located in the cap door on the north side of Top Hat Tower.\nThis moon is the secret moon hidden in one of the moving blocks, NOT the main moon

name: Searching the Frog Pond
description: This Moon is located in the cap door on the north side of the central plaza.\nThis moon is the main moon, NOT the secret moon

name: Secrets of the Frog Pond
description: This Moon is located in the cap door on the north side of the central plaza.\nThis moon is the main shards moon, NOT the secret moon

name: The Forgotten Treasure
description: This Moon is located in the cap door on the north side of the central plaza.\nThis moon is the secret moon at the top of the room, NOT the main moon

name: Taxi Flying Through Bonneton
description: This Moon is activated by capturing the binoculars on the north side of central plaza and looking at the taxi flying in the sky

name: Bonneter Blockade
description: This Moon is towards the bottom right side of the central plaza and is acquired by capturing a paragoomba and scaring away the bonneter blocking the moon

name: Cap Kingdom Regular Cup
description: This is the first koopa freerunning moon

name: Peach in the Cap Kingdom
description: This moon can be found on the north size of the central plaza and can be acquired by talking to peach

name: Found with Cap Kingdom Art
description: This moon can be found in Moon Kingdom by viewing the hint art on the side of the steps heading towards the north bridge. This moon is then acquired by groundpounding next to the collection of NPC's in post game Moon kingdom that are staring at earth

name: Next to Glasses Bridge
description: This moon can be found next to the bridge in the middle of the kingdom. Jump off the west side of the bridge and you should see it on top of a top hat building

name: Danger Sign
description: This moon can be found far on the west side of the kingdom and can be acquired by capturing a paragoomba and flying out to the danger sign

name: Under the Big One's Brim
description: This moon can be found under the brim of the Top Hat Tower and can be aquired by heading up to the top via warp or through the room then looking over the edge slight to the North West

name: Fly to the Edge of the Fog
description: This moon can be found all the way out at the far north east part of the kingdom and can be acquired by jumping off Top Hat Tower or capturing a paragoomba and flying over

name: Spin the Hat, Get a Prize
description: This moon can be activated on the bottom side of the central plaza by throwing cappy at the glowing Top Hat on the top of the arch

name: Hidden in a Sunken Hat
description: This moon can be activated out the south east side of the central plaza capturing a paragoomba and flying out to the Top Hat building with a glowing top piece, then throwing and holding cappy ontop of it

name: Fog-Shrouded Platform
description: This moon can be found over the edge of the north side of the central plaza. Groundpound the glowing spot of the platform to activate the moon

name: Bird Traveling in the Fog
description: This moon can be found all over the kingdom as the bird is on a cycle and will fly around the kingdom. This moon can be acquired by capturing a paragoomba and catching it

name: Caught Hopping Near the Ship!
description: This moon can be found on the hill north of the odyssey. Capture the bunny to get the moon

name: Taking Notes: In the Fog
description: This moon can be found on the west side of the kingdom and can be acquired by capturing a paragoomba and flying out to the building with the music night, then flying along and collecting all the music notes

name: Cap Kingdom Timer Challenge 2
description: This moon can be activated by throwing cappy on the scarecrow on the south east side of the central plaza, then grabbing the key to unlock the moon

name: Cap Kingdom Master Cup
description: This is the second koopa freerunning moon

name: Roll On and On
description: This is the moon at the end of the moon pipe moon found in the north west side of the central plaza, this is NOT the 'secret' moon

name: Precision Rolling
description: This is the moon found along the side path of the moon pipe moon found in the north west side of the central plaza, this is the 'secret' moon

name: Our First Power Moon
description: This is the first moon you get in the game, if you're genuinely missing this you're either on 1.0 and pulled a no no, or you miss clicked... which one is it

name: Multi Moon Atop the Falls
description: This is the mulimoon you obtain when you beat madame broode at the top of the kingdom

name: Chomp Through the Rocks
description: This moon can be found behind a rock wall and is accessible by capturing a chain chomp and knocking it open. It can be found north of where the t-rex is sleeping

name: Behind the Waterfall
description: This moon is found in the 8-bit section which is accessible by breaking open the big rock. Once inside you can reveal a hidden block along the left side then follow the path along to get the moon

name: On Top of the Rubble
description: This moon is found on some rubble north of the odyssey (in its revist location) along the east side of the kingdom

name: Treasure of the Waterfall Basin
description: This moon is found in a chest in a little alcove near the bridge in the middle of the kingdom

name: Above a High Cliff
description: This moon is found on top of the small cliff on the southern side of the west half of the kingdom

name: Across the Floating Isles
description: This moon can be found on the top section of the kingdom at the end of the floating islands on the north west side of the kingdom

name: Cascade Kingdom Timer Challenge 1
description: This moon can be acquired by activating the scarecrow right beside the bridge on the lower half of the kingdom

name: Cascade Kingdom Timer Challenge 2
description: This moon can be acquired by activating the scarecrow on the top part of the kingdom, in the Madame Broode arena

name: Good Morning, Captain Toad!
description: Captain toad can be found hanging out on a little platform off the top section of the kingdom. Head to the south west side of the arena and look down

name: Dinosaur Nest: Big Cleanup!
description: This moon can be found in the cap door on the south side of the west island. It can be acquired by going around and killing all of the Burrbo's

name: Dinosaur Nest: Running Wild!
description: This moon can be found in the cap door on the south side of the west island. It can be acquired by capturing the dino, heading off the far back ledge and breaking open one of the rocks to unlock the secret moon

name: Nice Shot with the Chain Chomp!
description: This moon can be found in the green pipe along the bottom path on the far north west side of the kingdom. This moon is the normal moon found simply at the end of the subarea

name: Very Nice Shot with the Chain Chomp!
description: This moon can be found in the green pipe along the bottom path on the far north west side of the kingdom. This moon is the secret moon which can be found in the room just past where you get the first main moon of the subarea

name: Past the Chasm Lifts
description: This moon is found in the cap door under the bridge at the northern back side of the kingdom. This moon is the normal moon found simply at the end of the subarea

name: Hidden Chasm Passage
description: This moon is found in the cap door under the bridge at the northern back side of the kingdom. This moon is the secret moon which can be found by riding one of the lifts (just before the final pipe of the subarea) to the top and running along the roof

name: Secret Path to Fossil Falls!
description: This moon is the painting moon which (in the case of an All Moons/100% run) can be grabbed by heading through the cascade painting in Seaside kingdom

name: A Tourist in the Cascade Kingdom
description: This moon is acquired by talking to the tourist who can be found near the taxi north of the odyssey (in its revisit location)

name: Rolling Rock by the Falls
description: This moon is acquired by breaking open the glowing moon in the central part of the kingdom (where the odyssey is originally at the beginning of the game). Can be quickly broken by attacking it with the dino or by throwing it in water

name: Peach in the Cascade Kingdom
description: This moon is acquired by talking to peach on the top side of the kingdom right by the exit of the 8-bit section

name: Cascade Kingdom Regular Cup
description: This moon is the first koopa freerunning moon

name: Caveman Cave-Fan
description: This moon is the second koopa freerunning mood

name: Shopping in Fossil Falls
description: This moon can be bought at the shop on the bottom north side of the kingdom

name: Sphynx Traveling to the Waterfall
description: This moon can be acquired by capturing the binoculars on the very south side of the kingdom, then zooming in and looking at the sphynx

name: Bottom of the Waterfall Basin
description: This moon can be activated by groundpounding the glowing spot under water underneath the bridge in the centre of the kingdom

name: Just a Hat, Skip, and a Jump
description: This moon can be found on the far east side of the back  section of the kingdom and requires you to activate some floating clouds to reach

name: Treasure Under the Cliff
description: This moon can be found at the back side of the kingdom near the bridge with all the Burrbos look up and against the wall and you should see it floating above some of the activatable clouds

name: Next to the Stone Arch
description: This moon can be found next to the bridge at the very top of the kingdom, look along the front side and you should see it floating over the edge

name: Guarded by a Colossal Fossil
description: This moon can be activated by holding cappy on the horn of the dinosaur skull at the top of the kingdom near the waterfall

name: Under the Old Electrical Pole
description: This moon requires you to capture the dinosaur, then bring it all the way back to the odyssey to knock the electrical pole. Once you've done so you can groundpound where it was to activate the moon

name: Under the Ground
description: This moon requires you to capture the dinosaur, then immidiately turn to your right and break the blocks directly next to the dinosaur. Then move the dino out of the way and groundpound the glowing spot to activate the moon

name: Inside the Busted Fossil
description: This moon is found at the top of the kingdom near the electrical wire/peach. Capture the chain chomp closest to the fossils near the waterfall, aim the chomp at the fossil near the electrical wire and when lined up properly, release to break open the fossil

name: Caught Hopping at the Waterfall!
description: This moon is acquired by catching the bunny which can be found near the shop

name: Taking Notes: Hurry Upward
description: This moon is acquired by entering the 2d section at the back of the kingdom, activating the music notes and collecting them all

name: Cascade Kingdom Master Cup
description: This moon is the second koopa freerunning moon

name: Across the Mysterious Clouds
description: This moon can be found in the moon pipe towards the back side of the kingdom. This moon is acquired by making your way to the end of the subarea and collecting it

name: Atop a Wall Among the Clouds
description: This moon can be found in the moon pipe towards the back side of the kingdom. This moon can be found on top of the first wall along the left side of the subarea

name: Across the Gusty Bridges
description: This moon can be found in the moon pipe around the centre of the kingdom, where the odyssey is first found in the beginning of the game. This moon can be acquired by making your way to the end of the subarea and collecting it

name: Flying Far Away from Gusty Bridges
description: This moon can be found in the moon pipe around the centre of the kingdom, where the odyssey is first found in the beginning of the game. This moon can be acquired by making your way to the left side of the subarea, throwing cappy into the boost at the right time to grab the lever at the end of the whirlwinds

name: Atop the Highest Tower
description: This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, found at the top of the 2d tower in the centre of the kingdom

name: Moon Shards in the Sand
description: This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, found on the west island. Go around and collect all the shards to spawn the moon

name: Showdown on the Inverted Pyramid
description: This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, given to you after the hariet boss fight at the top of the inverted pyramid

name: The Hole in the Desert
description: This moon is one of Sand Kingdom's story moons, given to you after the Knucklotec boss fight at the end of the hole where the inverted pyramid use to be

name: Overlooking the Desert Town
description: This moon can be found in the town near the beginning of the kingdom. It can be found at the top of one of the buildings near the last electrical pole

name: Alcove in the Ruins
description: This moon can be found in the ruin area in the middle of the kingdom. Underneath where the bullet bill spawns is a little alcove area where you will find this moon

name: On the Leaning Pillar
description: This moon can be found on a small pillar east of the ruins area just before the poison lake

name: Hidden Room in the Flowing Sands
description: This moon can be found in the most northern part of the quicksand portion of the ruins. Look along the west wall and you should see a segment that is raised above the sand. Sink just below this line while moving towards it, then start jumping once you're under it. You will then be in a small hidden room with the moon

name: Secret of the Mural
description: This moon can be found in the 2d tower in the centre of the kingdom. Make your way to the top of the 2d section but just before jumping up and out of the 2d section, head directly left instead to find a secret area where you will find the moon

name: Secret of the Inverted Mural
description: This moon is the secret moon in the 2d section of the inverted pyramid that goes around the outside. Just before you head through the final pipe, continue heading left where you will find a secret area and the moon

name: On Top of the Stone Archway
description: This  moon can be found on top of the archway that acts as the entrance to the ruins area. You can reach the top by either exiting out of the electrical wire, jumping off one of the ice pillars towards the side or making your way over with the bullet bill

name: From a Crate in the Ruins
description: This moon can be activated by breaking open the glowing crate next to the bullet bill spawner in the centre of the ruins

name: On the Lone Pillar
description: This moon is found on the lone pillar on the east side of the kingdom and can be reached by either a bullet bill or by grabbing glydon at the top of the kingdom

name: On the Statue's Tail
description: This moon can be activated by throwing cappy at the tail of one of the statues on top of the inverted period, on the north west side

name: Hang Your Hat on the Fountain
description: This moon can be activated by throwing cappy at the top of the water foundain in the centre of the town near the beginning of the kingdom

name: Where the Birds Gather
description: This moon can be activated by groundpounding the mound of sand on the eastern side of the little oasis area found to the east of the town near the beginning of the kingdom

name: Top of a Dune
description: This moon can be activated by groundpounding the top of the big hill found north west of the town near the beginning of the kingdom.

name: Lost in the Luggage
description: This moon can be activated by groundpounding the glowing spot of the ground found near a bunch of luggage to the east of and near the inverted pyramid

name: Bullet Bill Breakthrough
description: This moon can be acquired by capturing a bullet bill in the lower south east part of the ruins, then heading east you will find a hole in the wall. Head through the hole and break open the cage to grab the moon

name: Inside a Block Is a Hard Place
description: This moon can be acquired by capturing a bullet bill in the lower south east part of the ruins, then bringing it over and crashing it into the glowing block in the bottom south east corner of the ruins
